Art,<br><br>
A small suggestion.  There is a book called THE WRITER'S JOURNEY by Christopher Vogler.  The subtitle is MYTHICK STURCTURES FOR STORYTELLERS AND SCREENWRITERS.  It teaches how to tell stories through a &quot;Joseph Campbell Structure.&quot;<br><br>
I found that it, not only gave me ideas on how to write better, but lessons if life as well.  If you are interested, or find the time to read it, let me know what you think.  There's a run on sentence for you.  I'm sure I'll get some flak for that one, from an editor anyhow.<br><br>
Class Lass had a good question.  The nice thing I like about it; is that I know that we all can disagree and still remain brothers of choice.<br><br>
Paul<br>

